definition.value: Systemic venous tree (organ) the trunk of which, the superior vena cava, continues with the right atrium and the branches of which are distributed to the head, neck upper limbs, thorax and upper part of abdomen. Examples: There is only one superior systemiv venous tree.

ystemic venous tree (organ) the trunk of which, the inferior vena cava, continues with the right atrium and the branches of which are distributed to the abdomen, pelvis, perineum and the lower limbs. Examples: There is only one inferior systemiv venous tree.
